A list of manufactured parts and their properties
Manufacturing information for one part. Important properties are standardized. Besides that there is a key:value list to exchange further non-standardized properties for this part
You can use this key:value list for additional properties that were not defined in this aspect model.

This entity groups all meta information properties. Meta information properties give hints for a Catena-X data consumer to better understand, how this data set was created on the Catena-X data provider side.
This aspect model is used to exchange manufacturing-oriented information of several parts, e.g. for quality tasks

aas:langStringDefinitionTypeIec61360.aas:text: This aspect model is used to exchange manufacturing-oriented information of several parts, e.g. for quality tasks

The record operation enumeration can be used to realize delta update concept. Delta update concept means: - You transfer an initial load of data - After the first week only the delta to the initial load is transferred
The record status describes whether this record is: - new=>This record is transferred the first time - update=> Some properties of this record have changed compared to a previous transfer - delete=> This record was transferred in the initial load or in a previous delta update, but is not used any more and therefore it should be deleted on data consumer side - same=> This record was transferred in the initial load or in a previous delta update
Manufacturer-specific batch identifier: In which batch was this part manufactured
The fully anonymous and unique Catena-X ID of this part. This id is unique inside Catena-X data space.
The fully anonymous and unique Catena-X ID of this quality task. This id is unique inside Catena-X data space.
Indicator whether this part was reworked during manufacturing
Part name given from the manufacturer or supplier of this part, component, sub component or raw material. A manufacturer part name is NOT unique: All parts of the same kind share the same part name.

Part number given from the manufacturer or supplier of this part, component, sub component or raw material. A manufacturer part number is NOT unique: All parts of the same kind share the same part number.

Serial number given from the manufacturer or supplier of this part, component, sub component. A manufacturer serial number is unique: With the serial number the produced part can be traced within the manufacturer.
Number how often this part went through the EOL test
Unique Catena-X plant identifier, also called BPNS.
Country code of the plant, where the vehicle was produced.
Long name of the production plant of the vehicle
Plant id of the final assembly of the vehicle
Date of production for this specific part.
On which production line was this part produced
Key identifier for this additional information
Value for this additional information
You can use this key:value list for additional properties that were not defined in this aspect model.
A list of manufactured parts and their properties
Describes the selection criteria a Catena-X data provider has applied to create this data set.
Describes the starting point for providing records in this data set.
Describes the end point for providing records in this data set.
This meta information is valid for all entries in this data set. The meta information is used to tell the data consumer which selection criteria were applied by the data provider.
